nats.client

Interface HandlerRegistration


  • public interface HandlerRegistration
    Provides a registration for a handler such as a CompletionHandler or MessageHandler. This registration is used to remove the handler from the list of handlers that will be invoked when the pending operation completes.

    For example, when using a Subscription, you may add a MessageHandler using the Subscription.addMessageHandler(nats.client.MessageHandler) method. This method returns an instance of HandlerRegistration. When the remove() method is invoked, the MessageHandler is removed from the Subscription and will no longer be called when new messages arrive on the Subscription.

    Author:
    Mike Heath
